<span class="name"><a name="41328"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#4:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Snowkittie Heartilly</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=41328&amp;sid=6ed9964b8bc0a38b9bfce3ba4b228e89#41328"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Wed Jul 21, 2004 3:34 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
	<span class="gensmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;----</span><br>

<span class="postbody">Basically what Jurayn said.
<br />

<br />
Not sure how your guild distribute loots but... why you want to get a high end 2hb before monks do is beyond me. Unless you are in a DKP guild then you just save up points to beat everyone else, problem solve. But even so, I am in a DKP guild, 2nd on the monk/bst list, and I defer all 2hb to monks (up to Zha, we aren't in Time yet). Have a REBB since that one is so common it goes to alts/ applicants. That's exactly what Jurayn said - at several points there will be some 2hb that drops so often your whole guild will be outfitted with it. REBB is one, SoT in Time is another (well Zha maybe it's just our luck... for us it had been kinda rare), next one up is in Txevu I think, Staff of Revealed Secret 71/32 2hb, it's just a week or so when the top guild on our server had it rotting already. In general, unless you want to upgrade at every single level of 2hb, it will drop faster than you can loot it.
<br />

<br />
On the other hand.. convince them all h2h should go to bst first heh. At it is right now (till further AA addition/ skill cap raise etc.) you just do more dps with it.
<br />

<br />
DPS varies based on lots of thing, rough idea tho:
<br />
Monk:
<br />
Caen's Bo - ~140-160 dps
<br />
REBB - ~150-180
<br />
Zha - 180 - 230
<br />

<br />
Bst tho,
<br />
Caen's ~80
<br />
REBB ~80-100
<br />
And seem to have "low dps spike" alot.. I have counted a continuous 10 missed swings on a bad night, that's hitting mobs from the back.
<br />

<br />
True that delay on 2hb does help reduce some dps loss due to cast time, but I personally don't see it making up the loss from using equivalent 2hb over h2h... with spell haste the nuke goes off in about 1.5 sec, you aren't losing too much there if you time it good.
<br />

<br />
DS umm, only time I got problem with it is in adv when eveyrone's too lazy to dispell / reverse DS the mobs, mobs die fast regardless. Raid? Ermm nope, if the mob has a DS that actually causes problem, it will definitely be dealt with, otherwise it will for sure eat your local rogues faster than anyone else and they are more valuable DPS source than we are.
<br />

<br />
Enrage... or you mean riposte (in PoP)? When a 3k+ hitter enrages, 1 round of melee being riposted will get you killed/ low hp aggro, h2h or 2hb alike... If you don't have the habit to pause attack at mob 10%, you may want to do that now.. Mob self Memblur/ poor cornering / bad geometry / or if the tank just oops got dropped, you just cannot guarantee you have the mob's back all day long, and you don't want to be in front when it enrages. Our tank actually once flipped the twin birds in Fire when it started enraging and see which melee was afk, it was pretty hilarious to watch, tho the idea was, if you were alerted you wouldn't be killed in most case.
<br />

<br />
P.S. typed this at work over a few hours on and off.. now I dont know where I am going with this lol, but just going to put it in anyways...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
